    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a driver-focused example of high-revving Bavarian engineering. It features the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six power plant, equipped with individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system that pulls cleanly to its 7,900 RPM redline. The power is managed by a precise Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox and a mechanical limited-slip differential. Crucially, the rear subframe has been reinforced and the VANOS system serviced, addressing the primary technical concerns for this platform. With a taut chassis, refreshed bushings, and excellent throttle response, this M3 offers the raw, analog feedback that defines the Golden Era of M-cars.",
